<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-09-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="468" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                        <head><hi rend="italic"><persName type="from">Baron Fava</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lenox,
                                        Mass.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-09-19"><hi rend="italic">September 19,
                                    1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Anxious to learn the contents of New Orleans report and your
                            appreciations upon it. Am waiting for kind and prompt information,
                            urgently requested from my Government. Thanks.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Fava.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>